under the influence of the modernist writers and artists of the 1920s \"Lost Generation\" expatriate community. The Sun Also Rises, Hemingway's first novel, was published in 1926.\u003cbr /\u003e\u003cbr /\u003eAfter his 1927 divorce from Hadley Richardson, Hemingway married Pauline Pfeiffer. They divorced after he returned from Spanish Civil War where he had acted as a journalist, and after which he wrote For Whom the Bell Tolls. Martha Gellhorn became his third wife in 1940. They separated when he met Mary Welsh in London during World War II; during which he was present at the Normandy Landings and liberation of Paris.\u003cbr /\u003e\u003cbr /\u003eShortly after the publication of The Old Man and the Sea in 1952, Hemingway went on safari to Africa, where he was almost killed in two plane crashes that left him in pain and ill-health for much of the rest of his life. Hemingway had permanent residences in Key West, Florida, and Cuba during the 1930s and 1940s, but in 1959 he moved from Cuba to Ketchum, Idaho, where he committed suicide in the summer of 1961.","isGrAuthor":false,"works":{"__typename":"ContributorWorksConnection","totalCount":691},"profileImageUrl":"https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/authors/1574217836i/1455._UX200_CR0,25,200,200_.jpg","webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/author/show/1455.Ernest_Hemingway","user":null,"viewerIsFollowing":null,"followers":{"__typename":"ContributorFollowersConnection","totalCount":25228}},"Book:kca://book/amzn1.gr.book.v1.uKD_Ya4BYEXIumODzHsscw":{"id":"kca://book/amzn1.gr.book.v1.uKD_Ya4BYEXIumODzHsscw","__typename":"Book","legacyId":10799,"webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/10799.A_Farewell_to_Arms","title":"A Farewell to Arms","titleComplete":"A Farewell to Arms","description":"\u003ci\u003eA Farewell to Arms\u003c/i\u003e is the unforgettable story of an American ambulance driver on the Italian front and his passion for a beautiful English nurse. Set against the looming horrors 